506
00:21:41,601 --> 00:21:43,831
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

507
00:21:43,836 --> 00:21:45,796
- See this.

508
00:21:45,805 --> 00:21:47,805
Chase this.

509
00:21:47,807 --> 00:21:50,437
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

510
00:21:50,443 --> 00:21:52,713
It's the secret
to how to be you.

511
00:21:52,712 --> 00:21:56,352
- [chuckles]
- Okay. Back to the park.

512
00:21:56,349 --> 00:21:58,419
Let's finish this puppy.

513
00:21:58,418 --> 00:22:00,018
- Alice?

514
00:22:00,019 --> 00:22:01,949
[panting]

515
00:22:01,954 --> 00:22:03,894
Eliot?

516
00:22:03,890 --> 00:22:05,460
Alice!
- Chill, man.

517
00:22:05,458 --> 00:22:06,758
They can handle themselves.

518
00:22:06,759 --> 00:22:09,859
[footsteps tapping]
Shh, shh!

519
00:22:09,862 --> 00:22:11,532
What the hell was that?

520
00:22:11,531 --> 00:22:13,331
[echoing children's laughter]

521
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:15,933
- This house is haunted
as balls, is what that is.

522
00:22:15,935 --> 00:22:19,335
- [echoing]
Come in here, please.

523
00:22:29,682 --> 00:22:31,652
- Okay...

524
00:22:31,651 --> 00:22:32,821
<i> [eerie music]</i>

525
00:22:32,819 --> 00:22:35,049
- Hello?

526
00:22:35,054 --> 00:22:38,394
Anyone or anything?

527
00:22:38,391 --> 00:22:44,061
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

528
00:22:44,063 --> 00:22:46,803
[ball lightly thudding]

529
00:22:46,799 --> 00:22:51,469
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

530
00:22:51,471 --> 00:22:53,871
[distorted ringing and whirring]

531
00:22:53,873 --> 00:22:55,673
[tinkling music]

532
00:22:55,675 --> 00:22:57,405
Okay, Jesus, we get it.

533
00:22:57,410 --> 00:22:59,540
There are ghosts in here.

534
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:00,875
[electricity buzzes]

535
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,550
- I tag you.

536
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:04,518
You're it.

537
00:23:04,517 --> 00:23:06,677
[tinkling music continues]

538
00:23:06,686 --> 00:23:09,686
<i> [eerie music]</i>

539
00:23:09,689 --> 00:23:13,489
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

540
00:23:13,493 --> 00:23:15,893
- What just happened?

541
00:23:15,895 --> 00:23:17,955
- I tag you.
You're it.

542
00:23:17,964 --> 00:23:20,064
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

543
00:23:20,066 --> 00:23:22,926
- Do we go with this?

544
00:23:22,935 --> 00:23:26,035
- What other option
do we have?

545
00:23:26,038 --> 00:23:33,978
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

546
00:23:38,418 --> 00:23:40,478
- [groans]

547
00:23:40,486 --> 00:23:47,156
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

548
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:50,730
Okay, this is a little kinky,
even for me.

549
00:23:50,730 --> 00:23:53,930
- Would you care
for refreshment?

550
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:58,903
- Oh, um, okay, sure.
Sounds divine.

551
00:23:58,905 --> 00:24:02,035
Mmm. Okay.

552
00:24:02,041 --> 00:24:03,911
Thank you.

553
00:24:03,910 --> 00:24:07,180
We must get these things
off our hands.

554
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:08,750
Do you know Popper 29 yet?

555
00:24:08,748 --> 00:24:10,478
- No magic in the house.

556
00:24:10,483 --> 00:24:13,753
Be good, or she'll take you
to the quiet place.

557
00:24:13,753 --> 00:24:14,993
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

558
00:24:14,987 --> 00:24:17,587
- We'll be good.
Right, Eliot?

559
00:24:17,590 --> 00:24:20,060
- Mm, yeah,
you're the boss, kid.

560
00:24:20,059 --> 00:24:21,489
[electricity buzzes]

561
00:24:21,494 --> 00:24:23,464
- She's coming.

562
00:24:23,463 --> 00:24:25,063
[footsteps tapping,
door creaking]

563
00:24:25,064 --> 00:24:26,564
[electricity buzzes]

564
00:24:28,968 --> 00:24:30,068
[dishes rattle]

565
00:24:30,069 --> 00:24:33,069
<i> [foreboding music]</i>

566
00:24:33,072 --> 00:24:34,912
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

567
00:24:34,907 --> 00:24:36,167
- Stop doing that.

568
00:24:36,175 --> 00:24:37,905
[rope creaks]

569
00:24:37,910 --> 00:24:40,640
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

570
00:24:40,646 --> 00:24:43,876
- My brother is too soft,

571
00:24:43,883 --> 00:24:48,193
caring for you when he
needs peace to work.

572
00:24:48,187 --> 00:24:53,787
He has no idea
how naughty you truly are.

573
00:24:53,793 --> 00:24:55,933
Now drink your tea.

574
00:24:55,928 --> 00:25:03,868
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

575
00:25:03,870 --> 00:25:05,570
- [clears throat]

576
00:25:05,571 --> 00:25:07,671
- Drink it.

577
00:25:07,673 --> 00:25:11,913
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

578
00:25:11,911 --> 00:25:13,141
- [slurps]

579
00:25:13,145 --> 00:25:16,145
<i> [eerie music]</i>

580
00:25:16,148 --> 00:25:21,988
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

581
00:25:21,988 --> 00:25:24,718
- No.
I'm over here.

582
00:25:24,724 --> 00:25:25,894
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

583
00:25:25,892 --> 00:25:27,292
[giggles]

584
00:25:27,293 --> 00:25:31,033
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

585
00:25:31,030 --> 00:25:34,630
- Holy shit,
that's Christopher Plover.

586
00:25:34,634 --> 00:25:37,104
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

587
00:25:37,103 --> 00:25:39,073
Is it just me,
or does it feel like

588
00:25:39,071 --> 00:25:40,601
we're being shown something,
like how it was?

589
00:25:40,606 --> 00:25:42,566
- Yeah, the time slip.

590
00:25:42,575 --> 00:25:44,165
- You say that like,
"Yeah, a sunrise."

591
00:25:44,176 --> 00:25:46,206
- Sunderland talks
about it all the time.

592
00:25:46,212 --> 00:25:47,882
She has a PhD in hauntings.

593
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:49,680
Her favorite thing
about a haunted house is,

594
00:25:49,682 --> 00:25:52,122
you get these ghost movies
of the past running on a loop.

595
00:25:52,118 --> 00:25:54,018
You see shit like it was.

596
00:25:54,020 --> 00:25:55,250
- I didn't know any of that.

597
00:25:55,254 --> 00:25:56,724
- Of course not.
You're an idiot.

598
00:25:56,722 --> 00:25:57,922
[footsteps tapping]

599
00:25:57,924 --> 00:25:59,664
- Oh, my God,
it's her.

600
00:25:59,659 --> 00:26:01,329
- It's a tiny chick
in a beret.

601
00:26:01,327 --> 00:26:03,587
- Slow down, Jane.

602
00:26:03,596 --> 00:26:05,656
- That's Jane and Martin
from the books.

603
00:26:05,665 --> 00:26:07,795
- Nerdgasm.
- This makes sense.

604
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:09,630
Plover took them in,
and they spent their days

605
00:26:09,635 --> 00:26:11,065
playing with
the housekeeper's kids.

606
00:26:11,070 --> 00:26:12,670
Martin--he was, like,
really sick that summer--

607
00:26:12,672 --> 00:26:14,612
- Martin, hurry!

608
00:26:14,607 --> 00:26:15,867
<i> [light instrumental music]</i>

609
00:26:15,875 --> 00:26:17,735
- Janey, wait for me.

610
00:26:17,743 --> 00:26:19,983
Wait, no.
I'm coming with you.

611
00:26:19,979 --> 00:26:22,649
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

612
00:26:22,648 --> 00:26:25,048
Why won't you take me?

613
00:26:25,051 --> 00:26:28,591
Ember, Umber, why won't you
let me in anymore?

614
00:26:28,588 --> 00:26:30,788
[sighs]

615
00:26:30,790 --> 00:26:31,990
[door rattles closed]

616
00:26:31,991 --> 00:26:35,731
I try to be good.

617
00:26:35,728 --> 00:26:39,298
- Martin,
are you all right?

618
00:26:39,298 --> 00:26:40,758
Where's Jane?

619
00:26:40,766 --> 00:26:42,726
- Fillory.

620
00:26:42,735 --> 00:26:44,895
What's wrong with me?

621
00:26:44,904 --> 00:26:47,144
- [sighs]
Nothing.

622
00:26:47,139 --> 00:26:48,909
Some things
just aren't fair.

623
00:26:48,908 --> 00:26:50,668
We can't make sense of them.

624
00:26:50,676 --> 00:26:52,176
Let's have tea, hmm?
Come on.

625
00:26:52,178 --> 00:26:55,208
Us left-behinds
ought to stick together.

626
00:26:55,214 --> 00:26:58,784
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

627
00:26:58,784 --> 00:27:01,054
[electricity
buzzing and cracking]

628
00:27:01,053 --> 00:27:03,823
- She's coming.
We need to hide.

629
00:27:03,823 --> 00:27:05,323
- Quentin?

630
00:27:05,324 --> 00:27:07,394
- [inhales and sighs]

631
00:27:07,393 --> 00:27:10,263
- Okay, I'm getting
the fuáá out of here.

632
00:27:10,262 --> 00:27:12,232
- What did I tell
you children

633
00:27:12,231 --> 00:27:14,331
about disturbing
Mr. Plover?

634
00:27:21,874 --> 00:27:24,244
[liquid dripping]

635
00:27:24,243 --> 00:27:26,643
[chains clanking]

636
00:27:26,646 --> 00:27:29,646
<i> [foreboding music]</i>

637
00:27:29,649 --> 00:27:35,189
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

638
00:27:35,187 --> 00:27:36,717
- [sighs]

639
00:27:36,722 --> 00:27:37,922
Great.

640
00:27:37,923 --> 00:27:40,063
- No talking
in the quiet place.

641
00:27:40,059 --> 00:27:41,329
- Lady, I don't know
who you think I am, but--

642
00:27:41,327 --> 00:27:45,227
- Insolent is what you are.

643
00:27:45,231 --> 00:27:49,931
I've told you
I'll sew it shut.

644
00:27:49,935 --> 00:27:51,235
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

645
00:27:51,237 --> 00:27:53,237
- [whispers] Alice.

646
00:27:53,239 --> 00:27:57,309
<i> [frantic string music]</i>

647
00:27:57,309 --> 00:28:00,179
[speaking Arabic]

648
00:28:00,179 --> 00:28:01,809
[grunts]

649
00:28:01,814 --> 00:28:05,254
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

650
00:28:05,251 --> 00:28:08,791
Hey, hey, we need to hustle.

651
00:28:08,788 --> 00:28:10,688
Mrs. Danvers could come back.

652
00:28:10,690 --> 00:28:12,090
- Oh, my God.

653
00:28:12,091 --> 00:28:13,821
Do you know what this is?

654
00:28:13,826 --> 00:28:16,156
- A vaguely whimsical
horror show?

655
00:28:16,162 --> 00:28:17,862
- She did this.

656
00:28:17,863 --> 00:28:19,763
She really did this to
the children--Plover's sister.

657
00:28:19,765 --> 00:28:20,995
She tied them up
and drugged them

658
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:22,830
so that they wouldn't
disturb his work.

659
00:28:22,835 --> 00:28:25,165
- Okay, well, maybe ghost girl
can tell us where the button is.

660
00:28:25,171 --> 00:28:26,701
Hey, Beatrix?
[tapping]

661
00:28:26,706 --> 00:28:28,836
Beatrix, hey.
- [gasps]

662
00:28:28,841 --> 00:28:31,981
My tummy feels bad.

663
00:28:31,977 --> 00:28:34,307
[choking and gasping]
- Beatrix, it's okay.

664
00:28:34,313 --> 00:28:36,353
[coughing]

665
00:28:36,348 --> 00:28:38,778
How can we help her?
- I don't think we can.

666
00:28:38,784 --> 00:28:40,224
- [choking]
[liquid splattering]

667
00:28:40,219 --> 00:28:42,789
[panting and gasping]

668
00:28:42,788 --> 00:28:44,218
- [gasps]

669
00:28:44,223 --> 00:28:46,993
- Well, I guess we know
how she died.

670
00:28:46,992 --> 00:28:48,892
- Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

671
00:28:48,894 --> 00:28:51,364
- It's okay.
It's over.

672
00:28:51,363 --> 00:28:52,903
It's been over
for a long time.

673
00:28:52,898 --> 00:28:54,258
- No, no, no, no.
Not for her.

674
00:28:54,266 --> 00:28:56,026
She just keeps reliving it
over and over.

675
00:28:56,035 --> 00:28:57,065
We have to--
- We have to go.

676
00:28:57,069 --> 00:29:00,069
We have to go.

677
00:29:00,072 --> 00:29:01,472
- It's not the same.

678
00:29:01,474 --> 00:29:03,874
- Yeah, I know.
I'm sorry.

679
00:29:03,876 --> 00:29:06,076
Here, have another.

680
00:29:06,078 --> 00:29:08,878
- Hmm.

681
00:29:08,881 --> 00:29:12,081
- Let's spoil our dinner,
hmm?

682
00:29:12,084 --> 00:29:14,494
Oh, shall we work
a little?

683
00:29:14,487 --> 00:29:17,957
I think that might be nice.

684
00:29:17,957 --> 00:29:20,157
Do you think that
might be nice?

685
00:29:20,159 --> 00:29:22,359
<i> [light piano music]</i>

686
00:29:22,361 --> 00:29:24,291
- Martin, Mr. Plover,
I'm back.

687
00:29:24,296 --> 00:29:25,796
I was in Fillory.

688
00:29:25,798 --> 00:29:27,358
Martin, I brought you
what you asked for.

689
00:29:27,366 --> 00:29:29,226
You must have a look.
- We'll be right back, sir.

690
00:29:29,235 --> 00:29:32,365
She's dragging mud
all over the floor.

691
00:29:32,371 --> 00:29:36,771
<i> [eerie music]</i>

692
00:29:36,776 --> 00:29:38,106
- Stop that.
You're pinching me.

693
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:39,510
- You've got it?
- Yes.

694
00:29:39,512 --> 00:29:40,512
Let's go show Mr. Plover.

695
00:29:40,513 --> 00:29:43,083
- No, please.
Let's not.

696
00:29:43,082 --> 00:29:44,352
For me.

697
00:29:44,350 --> 00:29:45,950
- The button's a key.

698
00:29:45,951 --> 00:29:50,021
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

699
00:29:50,022 --> 00:29:52,422
- I know you're here.

700
00:29:52,424 --> 00:29:54,094
I know you're spying on us.

701
00:29:54,093 --> 00:29:56,463
George, come out.

702
00:29:56,462 --> 00:30:01,332
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

703
00:30:01,333 --> 00:30:03,103
Take this.

704
00:30:03,102 --> 00:30:04,842
It's a game, George.

705
00:30:04,837 --> 00:30:07,367
How well can you
hide the button?

706
00:30:07,373 --> 00:30:10,373
<i> [light instrumental music]</i>

707
00:30:10,376 --> 00:30:12,976
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

708
00:30:12,978 --> 00:30:15,048
- All right.

709
00:30:15,047 --> 00:30:17,347
Well, I--I won't forget
any of it, so...

710
00:30:17,349 --> 00:30:19,379
- I know you won't.

711
00:30:19,385 --> 00:30:22,045
Can I give you a little
advice in return?

712
00:30:22,054 --> 00:30:24,964
- Yeah.
- Forget that school.

713
00:30:24,957 --> 00:30:26,287
The world never did help
a smart girl.

714
00:30:26,292 --> 00:30:27,892
Why would it?

715
00:30:27,893 --> 00:30:31,093
We scare the shit
out of the world.

716
00:30:31,096 --> 00:30:34,196
If the world goes after you,
take it as a compliment.

717
00:30:39,471 --> 00:30:42,471
- You know, I could come back.
We could--we could do more.

718
00:30:42,474 --> 00:30:45,184
- This was really the big one.
- No, I know.

719
00:30:45,177 --> 00:30:47,907
I just--I just--you know,
I'm sure you have more things--

720
00:30:47,913 --> 00:30:49,313
- I do need
one other thing.

721
00:30:49,315 --> 00:30:51,375
- Yeah, sure.
Anything.

722
00:30:51,383 --> 00:30:54,993
- Kill me.

723
00:30:54,987 --> 00:30:56,947
- That's--that's crazy.

724
00:30:56,956 --> 00:30:59,516
- I'm allowed to be done.

725
00:30:59,525 --> 00:31:03,585
- No. I can't.
- Well, I need you to.

726
00:31:03,596 --> 00:31:05,256
- [gasps]

727
00:31:07,166 --> 00:31:08,996
You knew.

728
00:31:09,001 --> 00:31:10,501
You knew, and you did--

729
00:31:10,502 --> 00:31:11,972
No, I did not
sign up for this.

730
00:31:11,971 --> 00:31:13,501
- Then what?
Pleasantries?

731
00:31:13,505 --> 00:31:15,365
- No, how about
not killing anyone?

732
00:31:15,374 --> 00:31:17,374
- What do you think redemption
looks like, Julia?

733
00:31:17,376 --> 00:31:19,636
Being nice?
Donating shoes to Africa?

734
00:31:19,645 --> 00:31:23,445
You think that really burns
the tumors off your soul?

735
00:31:23,449 --> 00:31:25,249
- What if she's wrong?

736
00:31:25,251 --> 00:31:28,291
You know, what if a Magician
finds a cure tomorrow?

737
00:31:28,287 --> 00:31:30,987
What if there really is a hell
and this takes me there?

738
00:31:30,990 --> 00:31:33,520
- You're already in hell.
So is she.

739
00:31:37,496 --> 00:31:40,156
- What am I
supposed to do?

740
00:31:40,165 --> 00:31:42,495
- Whichever's hardest.

741
00:31:45,137 --> 00:31:47,267
- [exhales]

742
00:31:51,911 --> 00:31:54,241
- Oh, thank you.

743
00:31:54,246 --> 00:31:57,376
- Drink up, Jane,
and eat.

744
00:31:57,383 --> 00:31:59,383
You must be famished.

745
00:31:59,385 --> 00:32:02,445
<i> [violin music]</i>

746
00:32:02,454 --> 00:32:11,434
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

747
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:14,060
- Jane, don't you
want to join us?

748
00:32:14,066 --> 00:32:17,326
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

749
00:32:17,336 --> 00:32:20,496
- Oh, she's tired.

750
00:32:20,506 --> 00:32:22,206
That's all right.

751
00:32:22,207 --> 00:32:26,237
You go ahead, Martin,
like last time.

752
00:32:26,245 --> 00:32:30,475
- I don't know
if I want to.

753
00:32:30,482 --> 00:32:32,352
- Remember when I took
you and your sister

754
00:32:32,351 --> 00:32:35,151
to town for cinema?

755
00:32:35,154 --> 00:32:37,024
Bought her that dress
she wanted.

756
00:32:37,022 --> 00:32:38,262
- Yes.
We're grateful.

757
00:32:38,257 --> 00:32:40,287
- When I was a boy,

758
00:32:40,292 --> 00:32:42,962
I didn't have anyone
who thought about me.

759
00:32:42,962 --> 00:32:47,102
I saw it wouldn't happen
to any child I cared about.

760
00:32:47,099 --> 00:32:49,599
I care about you,
Martin.

761
00:32:51,203 --> 00:32:53,573
Come on, in front
